content:
Access Data When You're Offline

View and analyze data on your mobile device when internet access isn't available.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To enable offline access, tap the three dots next to a dashboard or dataset, then tap Make Available Offline. When the asset finishes downloading, you're ready to take data analysis anywhere.

Analytics uses live data whenever you have internet access. Offline assets aren't automatically updated when internet access is available. Tap Refresh Offline Data to keep your offline data fresh.

To see all assets available for offline access, tap the filter icon and select Offline. To remove offline access for a specific asset, open the details panel and tap the check mark above Available Offline. To remove all offline access, go to Settings, tap Offline, and then tap Remove all offline data.

Keep in mind that:

* Offline data is downloaded using Wi-Fi only.
* Assets exceeding 750 MB or the device's storage capacity aren't available for offline access.
* Mobile Offline settings apply to individual mobile devices and aren't synced across multiple devices.

Some features aren't supported for offline dashboards and lenses, including custom maps, linking, personal views, Save, Save As, Post to Chatter, Share via Email, APEX, and SOQL.
title: Accessing Data Offline with Salesforce CRM Analytics
